{
  "stem": "24090.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was tiny, and it had two stories because the women sat upstairs, although this was a Jewish reform synagogue, the German type of reform.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember the Hebrew prayers, and also German was spoken in there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't remember much about context-- context of what was said in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But after we went to the synagogue for the services, she and I walked to the cemetery, which was also located in Opladen, and we visited my dad's grave.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I have real clear collections from a very early time that his grave was located at the end of the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You walked through an iron gate into the cemetery, and we walked straight down.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And on the right side, there was a big birch tree, with a big trunk, and you know, how the branches come down.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was an intriguing, peaceful type of a tree, right next to his grave.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we spent time there every holiday.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I'm glad I had that recollection, because I had to identify that grave site later on when I went back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that was one of the strong reasons I went there, because I had no real love of going back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I almost didn't go when they invited me back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But one of our missions was to identify Dad's grave and re-erect a stone.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It had completely vanished when I came back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There wasn't a stone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I recall a-- a marble stone that was wide on his grave, with his name, of course, on there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was destroyed totally.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Nazis, during the war years.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The desecrated that whole cemetery, right.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
